aima.core.search.csp

Class Domain

  • java.lang.Object
    • aima.core.search.csp.Domain
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>

    public class Domain
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.Object>
    A domain Di consists of a set of allowable values {v1, ... , vk} for the corresponding variable Xi and defines a default order on those values. This implementation guarantees, that domains are never changed after they have been created. Domain reduction is implemented by replacement instead of modification. So previous states can easily and safely be restored.
    Author:
    Ruediger Lunde
